[src:managed-kubernetes/kubernetes] *Attribute-based access control (ABAC) mode*: Grants access rights to users through the use of defined access control policies which combine attributes together.
[src:managed-kubernetes/kubernetes] *Role-based access control (RBAC) mode*: Grants access rights to users based on roles that are granted to the user, where each role defines a list of actions that are allowed.
[src:managed-kubernetes/kubernetes] *Webhook mode*: Queries a REST API service to determine if a user is authorized to perform a given action.
